PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1784908087
OL,3,CFather jailed for life after murdering
OL,4,Cnewborn baby by shaking him
OL,6,FWatch police bodycam footage of
OL,7,Fofficers speaking to Tony Bartlett
OL,9,FA father who murdered his four-week-
OL,10,Fold son by shaking him has been jailed
OL,11,Ffor a minimum of 18 years.
OL,13,FAtticus Bartlett died in hospital
OL,14,Fafter collapsing at his family home in
OL,15,FChard, Somerset, on 16 July 2022.
OL,17,FHis father, Tony Bartlett, 39, of
OL,18,FAxminster, Devon, was convicted of
OL,19,Fmurder following a trial at Bristol
OL,20,FCrown Court.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G1/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40102
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1784908087
OL,3,CFather jailed for life after murdering
OL,4,Cnewborn baby by shaking him
OL,6,FThe jury found Bartlett violently
OL,7,Fshook Atticus, causing severe internal
OL,8,Finjuries to the baby's brain and
OL,9,Fspinal cord.
OL,11,FMr Justice Cavanagh jailed Bartlett,
OL,12,Fformerly a postman, for life and
OL,13,Fordered him to serve a minimum of 18
OL,14,Fyears in prison.
OL,16,FThe judge told Bartlett he was "very
OL,17,Fdrunk" when he carried out the fatal
OL,18,Fattack on Atticus, adding: "I have no
OL,19,Fdoubt that this terrible tragedy would
OL,20,Fnot have happened if you were not so
OL,21,Fheavily intoxicated."
OL,26,@xD@`OUyD@FO]zD@\OU}D@UO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G2/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1784908087
OL,3,CFather jailed for life after murdering
OL,4,Cnewborn baby by shaking him
OL,6,FHe said Bartlett had been feeding
OL,7,FAtticus with a bottle and the baby was
OL,8,Fbringing up the milk.
OL,10,F"In your drunken state, Atticus's
OL,11,Finability to take the bottle as well
OL,12,Fas you thought he should enraged you,"
OL,13,Fthe judge said.
OL,15,F"You had a sudden fit of anger. You
OL,16,Fvented that anger on your tiny baby
OL,17,Fson. You shook him very violently
OL,18,Findeed, gripping him very tightly
OL,19,Fround his ribcage.
OL,26,@rD@AOUtD@fO]wD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,402,400,120,260,000,100
PN,40104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F401A1784908087
OL,3,CFather jailed for life after murdering
OL,4,Cnewborn baby by shaking him
OL,6,F"This only lasted a few seconds or at
OL,7,Fmost a minute or so. Just in that
OL,8,Fbrief moment, you wanted to cause
OL,9,FAtticus serious injury.
OL,11,F"As suddenly as you began, you
OL,12,Fstopped, your anger evaporated, and
OL,13,Fthen you dozed off."
OL,15,FDuring the trial, Charles Row KC said
OL,16,FBartlett had been "drunk and
OL,17,Ffrustrated" when he attacked his
OL,18,Fnewborn son.
OL,26,@nD@AOUsD@AOUuD@TO]xD@SOUyD@KO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G4/13
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
